---
description: "Laravel security rules for auction/bidding (authz, rate limiting, atomic bids)"
globs:
  - "**/*.php"
---

## Authentication
- Prefer **Laravel Sanctum** for SPA auth (cookie-based) unless the repo explicitly uses tokens/JWT.
- Never log secrets. Never commit `.env`.

## Authorization (required)
- Every endpoint that mutates state MUST have explicit authorization:
  - listing create/update/delete
  - auction create/start/end/cancel
  - bid placement
  - admin actions (approve/remove listings, manage users)
- Implement via **Policies/Gates**; controllers call `authorize(...)` (or middleware) consistently.

## Input validation (required)
- Use `FormRequest` for non-trivial endpoints.
- Validate money/bid amounts as numeric with clear constraints (min, max, precision).

## Atomic bid placement (required)
- Placing a bid MUST be atomic:
  - wrap in a DB transaction
  - lock the auction row (or relevant row) to prevent race conditions
  - re-check auction status/time inside the lock
  - enforce minimum increment and “cannot bid on your own listing”
- Return a conflict response when outbid/race happens (e.g. 409) with the latest highest bid.

## Rate limiting & abuse prevention
- Rate limit bid placement routes (per-user + per-IP).
- Add server-side checks to prevent:
  - bids after auction end
  - repeated identical bids in very short windows (optional)

## Admin panel safety
- Admin routes must be behind `auth` + role/permission middleware and policy checks.
- Log admin actions (who did what, when) for moderation features.

## Data privacy & uploads
- For listing images: validate content type/size; store in non-public disk or sanitized public path; never trust client filenames.
